{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Validate required patient fields before downstream processing; return one clear error listing all missing required fields.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Seam-map: module/interface seam between intake orchestrator and validation/downstream services. The failure is not just field-check logic; it is that missing fields must prevent downstream calls. A realistic test must wire orchestrator + validator + downstream stubs and assert zero downstream invocation plus aggregated missing-field error output. Rejected System/Agentic/Workflow because behavior text is limited to pre-processing validation and error reporting, with no required real OS/network/model seam.","test_description":"Run intake entrypoint with payloads missing one and multiple required fields. Assert response includes all missing field names and assert insurance/triage/scheduling modules are not called.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Reject invalid DOB values: future dates, dates older than 150 years, and non-date strings.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Seam-map: local function seam (date parsing/range validation). This behavior is pure validation logic with deterministic inputs/outputs and no cross-module or infrastructure dependency. Rejected Integration+ because behavior text only requires correctness of DOB parsing/range rules.","test_description":"Table-driven tests on DOB validator covering future date, now-150y boundary, older-than-150y, invalid strings, and valid dates.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Insurance eligibility request uses correct patient ID and plan code and correctly maps payer responses: eligible, not eligible, pending.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Seam-map: environment seam (real HTTP interaction with payer API). Real failures often occur in serialized request shape, transport-level behavior, and HTTP response handling that in-process mocks can miss. Minimum reliable boundary is a real HTTP server/socket test. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because payer statuses are deterministic API outputs, not model judgment or multi-agent sequencing.","test_description":"Start a test HTTP server; execute eligibility check over real network calls; assert outbound payload contains exact patient ID/plan code; return each status response and assert internal state mapping to eligible/not eligible/pending.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.28,"System":0.62,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"If payer API is unreachable, mark eligibility as pending and continue intake instead of blocking.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Seam-map: environment seam (network failure/unreachable API). The failure mode is specifically transport unreachability; mocking exceptions can hide real timeout/connection-error paths. Minimum is a real network failure simulation (unbound port, refused connection, timeout). Rejected Agentic/Workflow because behavior concerns deterministic fallback control flow around network failure, not model quality or multi-agent chain.","test_description":"Invoke intake against a non-routable/unavailable payer endpoint (or forced real timeout). Assert eligibility becomes pending and subsequent intake steps still execute.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.14,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"AI symptom triage assigns high urgency for emergency symptom combinations (e.g., chest pain + shortness of breath).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Seam-map: model-judgment seam. Correctness depends on real AI medical reasoning output quality; deterministic stubs would always pass and miss misclassification failures. Rejected Workflow because this behavior evaluates one agentic decision step, not multi-agent sequencing.","test_description":"Run triage with real model calls on a curated emergency symptom set and verify urgency classification is high with acceptance thresholds over repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.15}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Symptom triage outputs clinician-reviewable natural-language rationale, not only a numeric urgency score.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Seam-map: model-judgment seam for generated explanation quality/presence. Whether explanation is meaningful and present depends on real model generation behavior; mocks hide this. Rejected Workflow because this is still a single triage generation step rather than a multi-step agent pipeline.","test_description":"Call real triage model with representative symptom cases; assert output includes non-empty natural-language explanation meeting basic clinical readability/structure checks in addition to urgency score.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.13}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"Scheduling chooses first available slot consistent with urgency SLA (high: same-day, medium: within 48h).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Seam-map: module/interface seam between urgency assignment, scheduling policy, and calendar persistence. Needs multiple modules plus DB state interaction, but no required real network/subprocess/model judgment. Integration-brake: (a) no explicit OS/network requirement in behavior text, (b) no AI correctness dependency here, (c) no multi-agent chain.","test_descripti